1 Download The Triaxis Official Artwork Theme Slasher Here
2 Then Click Save Image As
3 Save It To Download Then Name It To Slasher.png
4 Then Create Folder Name Slasher
5 Then Move Slasher.png To Folder Name Slasher
6 Open Terminal Then sudo mv /home/yourusername/Slasher /usr/share/wallpapers/
7 On KDE Plasma 
  Right‑click on the desktop → Configure Desktop and Wallpaper. Under Wallpaper, choose Image. Click Open and select your Slasher wallpaper file.
  Adjust scaling (Scaled, Centered, or Fill) depending on your preference.
  Apply → the Slasher Wallpaper
  
  On GNOME
  Open Settings → Appearance.
  Under Background, click the image selector.
  Choose your Slasher wallpaper file.
  GNOME lets you set different images for light mode and dark mode if desired.
  Apply → the Slasher becomes your GNOME background.

  On Sway (Wayland tiling WM)
  Edit your Sway config file (usually ~/.config/sway/config).
  Add a line like:
  output * bg /usr/share/wallpapers/Slasher/Slasher.png fill
  fill ensures it scales properly.
  Save the config and reload Sway (Super+Shift+C).

  On XFCE
  Right‑click on the desktop → Desktop Settings.
  Under Background, click Folder or Image.
  Select your Slasher wallpaper file.
  Choose style (Scaled, Zoom, Centered, etc.).
  Apply

8 You Can Select Slasher On SDDM
  Open System Settings.
  Go to Startup and Shutdown → Login Screen (SDDM).
  In the Theme section, pick the theme you want (e.g., Lubuntu, or any custom one).
  Click Background (some themes show this option directly).
  Browse and select your Slasher wallpaper image.
  Apply changes.
  Restart or log out
